\b\fs40 \cf4 Starting Screen\

\b0\fs36 \cf0 When the app is opened, the app looks for beans in its vicinity. If any are found, a dialog pops up with a list of the beans so that the user can choose the bean to connect with. If not, the connection screen.\
The connection screen is a simple empty screen with a light pastel background and a big round button in the centre with the word \'93Connect\'94. When the button is pressed, it gets darker - making it appear to have been pressed and once again Light Blue Beans are searched for in the vicinity and if found, the dialog opens up. If not, the app returns to the connection screen and a toast appears with the words \'93No beans found\'94. \
The dialog that opens up contains a list of all the beans available in the vicinity of the smartphone to be chosen and connected to and to be used. \
	\
If a bean is connected to which is not designed for working with Phantom Guitar\'ae the bean flashes a red light thrice and the app returns to the connection screen and a toast appears with the words \'93Light Blue Bean incompatible\'94.\
If a bean is connected to properly, the led on the bean turns green and the app moves on to the mode selection screen.\
\

\b\fs40 \cf4 Mode Selection Screen\

\b0\fs36 \cf0 The Screen for Selection of Mode is basically the home page to return to once a bean is connected. So this has a light pastel background and a faint outline of an electric guitar in the background. Also there is a faint outline of a phantom/ghost/skull face. \
Now the two buttons for selection of the different modes are large rectangles that when you press, get filled and thus show that they have been pressed. The two buttons have the text \'93Chord on-the-go mode\'94 and \'93Chord Progression Mode\'94.\
To go back to the connection/starting screen - press the back button. A dialog will open up asking the user if he/she really wishes to disconnect the bean. If yes is selected, the app returns to the connection screen. If no is selected, nothing happens i.e. the app stays on the mode selection screen.\
\
